title: For Sale/Trade:  S&W Model 52 (NO DASH) RARE  38 master Target Pistol
postcontent:
This is a gun that will only come around once in a lifetime.  There were only 3,500 52 no dash guns made.  This is one of them.  Has box, paper work, two mags, barrel tool, and it is in 99% condition.  This is a collectors Holy Grail.  I know it will take a special buyer.  I have included a link to an article from Shooting times about the gun.  Below is an excerpt from that article. This is not a 52-1 or 52-2... The 52 no dash was the only gun to go through rigorous testing before it left SW.  Do not low ball me.  Do not waste my time.


According to History of Smith & Wesson by S&W historian Roy Jinks, “To insure the accuracy of the pistol, extra rigid inspection was incorporated by having the Model 52 machine rest tested at 50 yards to insure that the pistol would shoot five-shot groups having maximum spread of two inches. Any pistol that could not meet this standard was returned to production for reworking.”

Insistence upon such tight tolerances meant that production was slow, and only 3,500 units were produced by 1963.

http://www.shootingtimes.com/2010/09/23/handgun_reviews_st_swmodel5238_200906/

title: For Sale:  Sig Sauer 556 Russian Swat Quad Rail  7.62 x 39 AK not AR
postcontent:
THE LEGEND CONTINUES. The performance and accuracy of the Swiss-built SG 550 tactical rifle is found in every SIG556. The Russian SWAT is a semi automatic rifle with the silhouette that harkens back to the original military-only 550 model. Featuring a full length gas piston operating system with a 2-position gas valve, the rifle will keep operating even when the environmental conditions deteriorate.   

The "Russian" version comes in 7.62 x 39. The 556 Russian SWAT features a Swiss-type folding stock, as well as a aluminum quadrail forend that is ideally suited for mounting accessories. The Russian SWAT’s sleek profile and compact length is enhanced by a 16’’ barrel. The quad rail front end has loads of space to add whatever type of lasers, lights or sights that you may want or need.   

I bought this rifle last summer along with (8) additional Tapco Polymer magazines.  I have used (4) of the mags to test their functionality while the other (4) are still in their original packaging.  I am also including the original factory magazine bringing the total number to nine.  

It packs a lot of punch with the 7.62 x 39 / AK 47 round whose ballistics are almost identical to the much more expensive .300 aac blackout.  It eats up any kind of ammo you throw at it thanks to its piston driven system.  Unlike the AR 15's direct impingement system that vents into the open block the piston system can run "dirty ammo" with little fear of gumming up the works.  

The side folding stock allows this rifle to close down to a compact 26" length. The design allows operation with the stock open or closed.  When it is closed, this rifle is great in confined spaces. It comes standard with a "One Point Sling" attachment point to enhance its versatility.  

I have added a UTG aluminum fore grip which has a waterproof storage accessible by unscrewing the bottom.  The fore grip is attached to the forward quad rail via a quick release cam lever.     

For optics, I have added a Holographic Reflex 552 Sight.  The reticle is the "Dot in Circle" style that is switchable from Red to Green with adjustable brightness.  

The rifle also has A.R.M.S. front and rear BUIS (back up iron sights).  These are super low profile so they stay out of the way when not in use. The metal aperature on the back sight is selectable between a large close quarters opening or a small pin hole opening for longer ranges.  

The iron sights perfectly "Co-Witness" with the holographic sight.  The tip of the front post has the appearance of being illuminated when you are viewing the iron sights with the reflex sight turned on.  

I have the original box, manual, and pad lock. I am also throwing in the woodland camo (4) AK magazine pouch seen in the picture.  

I am selling this beautiful piece of Swiss Steel because I have a new baby on the way.  I am not interested in trades.    $1450 for the rifle and accessories. Cash Only - FTF transactions. I am not interested in any trades.  

I also have about 1800 rounds of 7.62 x 39 steel case ammo available for sale.  Ask me about a package deal with the rifle.

The BCMGUNFIGHTER™ Charging Handle and extended latches feature internal redesigns to direct the force off of the roll pin and into the body of the charging handle during support hand only manipulations. 

This new design has a built in backstop engineered into the extended latch and into the charging handle. As the latch is opened up, its’ travel is limited by these flat surface backstops.With this travel limiting feature, the stress is taken off the roll pin, and is now redirected into the entire body of the charging handle.

The BCMGUNFIGHTER™ Charging Handle offers two significant advantages.
1. Since the tiny roll pin is no longer the weak point - it is a much stronger system and tactical latch will stay intact even under repeated support side only manipulation.
2. With the force kept inside the body of the handle, when the handle is pulled directly to the rear, it moves directly to the rear and does not angle off to the outboard side. A much smoother operation.
